From 7c6e3830466a5882991e64e68996cb285c5fddb8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lids Labs <55252374+lidslabs@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 00:27:07 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 16/22] lidslabs v0.4.0: retune Swiftfin corrections for v1.5
 two-engine profiles

Swiftfin tvOS v1.5 ships two player engines (VLCKit + AVPlayer) that post
distinct DeviceProfiles under the same client string (Name=null on both),
and rewrote its profiles so two prior over-claims are gone.

- Force HEVC for Swiftfin via the client gate (not the Name map, which
  cannot match Name=null). Fixes HDR sources transcoding to h264 -> SDR
  tonemap; forced HEVC keeps the HDR-passthrough path engaged.
- Rework the DV P7 strip: v1.5 now declares a hevc VideoRangeType list that
  still includes DOVIWithELHDR10Plus, so the old !alreadyRestricted skip was
  the wrong branch. Actively remove EL ranges (DOVIWithEL/DOVIWithELHDR10Plus)
  from every declared hevc VideoRangeType condition; append an EL-free list
  only when none is declared. P5/P8/HDR10 stay direct-play.
- Remove the TrueHD strip (v1.5 no longer advertises truehd direct-play; the
  AC3 compat track is selected natively) and the Swiftfin fMP4 force (v1.5
  defaults its HLS transcode container to mp4/fMP4).
